Blurb::
Address any model misordering in MFMC numerical solutions by reordering on the fly.

Description::
The ordering of the model hierarchy is continuously redefined for MFMC
as needed to allow for proper evaluation of estimator variance
expressions.  Specification of a model order in the ensemble surrogate
model specification is only used as the starting point for the algorithm.

On-the-fly model reordering can result in lower estimator variance, but
it can affect solution robustness (due to discontinuous gradients) and
complicate comparisons with published MFMC implementations.

Topics::

Examples::

.. code-block::

    method,
	multifidelity_sampling
	  numerical_solve override
	  model_reordering auto_reorder   # default
	solution_mode online_pilot
	pilot_samples = 50 seed = 8674132
	max_function_evaluations = 500

